State.Name: Crows- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Crystal Golems are large masses of faceless and vaguely humanoid crystal, animated by unknown means, that patrol Blackreach. Despite Azura's Moonshadow and Meridia's Colored Rooms being almost inaccessible to mortals, it's certain that some roam that realms since they're often summoned on Nirn by azura's and meridia's worshipers.
State.Name: Crystal Golems - Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Cthulhoids are robust vaguely humanoid daedra with greenish warty skin, having as main characteristic a disturbing head that resembles that of an octopus, with tentacles coming out of the chin, and a mouth full of several rows of sharp teeth. Poisonous, their bodies produce a constant toxic secretion.
State.Name: Cthulhoids- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Cursed Child's Dolls are a type of Poltergeist, in common sense Poltergeists are an artificial type of half-independent entity created unconsciously by sentient mortal beings, as a response to feelings like fear or anger. They commonly possess objects and corrupt them, in this case they turned dolls into bloody killer toys.
State.Name: Cursed Child's Doll - 2017 Halloween Special (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Minotaurs are a powerfull beast-race with physical features of both man and bull. The forest dweller cyrodilic ones are the most degenerated descendants of Morihaus and the now extinct Alessian Empire's minotaur civilization. This variant is feral, and bulkier than their Skyrim's cousins, but use more primitive armoury.
State.Name: Cyrodilic Minotaurs - Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Czarts are a brawny three-eyed ungulate daedras with antlers that resembles a were-elk and are related to Hircine and his hunting grounds. They are speed and brute strength personified, rivaled on this only by few amongst daedras. Forsworn and Hagravens commonly use a smaller type known as Howlers as guard dogs.
State.Name: Czarts- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Durzogs, sometimes called sludgepuppies, are carnivorous animals not dissimilar to reptilian dogs. They have striped green scaly skin, six red eyes, spines on their back, head, legs and tail, and large teeth and claws designed for tearing. Durzogs are often domesticated by goblin tribes for hunting, guard and to fight on wars between clans.
State.Name: Durzogs - Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Dwarven Colossus are one of the magnum opus amongst Animunculi,  they are massive, with incredible endurance and fire power. They possess specialized weapons on their arms, a large dual-blade gauntlet on the right and a hammer piston that creates fire pulses on the left. They are also able to breath extremely destructive fire.
State.Name: Dwarven Colossus - Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Created to be the pawns on the front line of the Dwemer army, Dwarven Defenders are articulated automatons designed to emulate the combat skills of their creators in wars and conflicts. Wielding light dwarven shields, and sledgehammers, and firing blasts of electricity through their central core, these machine armies are a force to be feared.
State.Name: Dwarven Defenders- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: The big Dwarven Magettas are firebreathing powerfull dwemer automatons that patrol the now abandoned Dwarven Ruins. Lighter and less armored than a Centurion, what a Magetta loses in defence and offensive raw strength, it gains in agility, mobility and fire power. Also being composed internally by lava, they produce a tremendous heat around them.
State.Name: Dwarven Magetta- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Dwarven Sentinels are created simply as killing machine designed for one thing: search and destroy anyone who invade the dungeons of their masters. Strangely evil, they appear as a multi-tentacled creature, with multiple glowing red sensors, that moves effortlessly through the air, probably using an advanced internal form of electromagnetism.
State.Name: Dwarven Sentinels- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: A simple but lethal war machine, these fast top-shaped small dwemer automatons, covered with multiple motion sensors, extremely sharp metal spines installed around their metal bodies and in constant spinning movement, are the ideal machine to chase and reach invaders inside the dwemer ruins, or to cause great casualties on the battlefield.
State.Name: Dwarven Spinners- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Dwemers used to adapt some of their war automatons to perform trivial functions. Some of them were Dwarven Ballistas who had their bolt launching platform removed, and in its place were installed sets of spinning blades typically used as traps in dwemer ruins. These modified automatons were used for harvesting and became known as Dwarven Threshers.
State.Name: Dwarven Threshers- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

Companions believe they are people with weak minds and bodies that received this blessing of Hircine, but were unable to dominate the form, resulting in mindless feral werewolves, that walk in 4 legs and can't return to the human form. Some speculate they are cursed Silver-Hands.

State.Description: Lucien is a fully voiced Imperial follower with over 5000 lines of immersive, lore-friendly dialogue. Though he arrives in Skyrim as a cowardly scholar, he'll gradually gain strength and confidence by your side until he grows into a hero in his own right.

State.Description: Lurchers are a bulked up corrupted variant of Spriggan, created by mages and witches. They can be found on swamps and forests being used as guardians. State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Among the various daedra clans, there are those that are most comfortable wearing lighter armor, compared to the traditional heavy daedric equipment. Light daedric armor offers good protection, without weighing too much, and offering greater mobility to its users, being preferred among important clans such as the Skaafins and Xivkyns.
State.Name: Daedric Light Armor- Mihail Armors and Clothes (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: A symbol of the pride of the Dremora clan, this heavy daedric armor seems at first glance uncomfortable and cumbersome, although terrifying for anyone who sees it approaching on the battlefield. This view is not at all wrong, since in fact it stands out in weight, but at the same time, it offers protection above the common daedric set.
State.Name: Dremora Armor- Mihail Armors and Clothes (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: A symbol of the recent past of cruelty of the Great House Dres of Morrowind, worn by the merciless slavemasters and created to inspire fear, and to destroy the hopes and self-esteem of slaves, this outfit made from Argonian and Khajiit leather, and adorned with their bones , is undoubtedly an unsettling view.
State.Name: Dres Slavemaster Outfit- Mihail Armors and Clothes (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail

State.Name: Harbinger Armor- Mihail Armors and Clothes (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: A true master of necromancy needs an armor that matches his evil mind. Made of pure ebony metal shaped in a terrifying design, adorned with fabrics decorated by dark arcane writing, and enchanted by powerful magic, whoever wears the Necromaster Robes will make even the inhabitants of Soul Cairn tremble.
State.Name: Necromaster Robes- Mihail Armors and Clothes (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: If you're the kind of alchemist who specializes in venoms and poison-making, you must have this special protective garb to keep yourself safe from being poisoned by your own experiments—or else! And if your clients are just a little bit intimidated by your creepy attire, all the better.
State.Name: Toxin Doctor Outfit- Mihail Armors and Clothes (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Your restorarion skills will achieve a new level with this powerfull area spell, made specially for arch-healers and master light magic users. Using it you can cast Grand Healing Orbs to aid and heal you and your allies in combat. These orbs not only heal, but also deals great damage to undead, including the most powerfull amongst them.
State.Name: Grand Healing Orb- Mihail Powers and Spells (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail

Use this skills to create impenetrable barriers, dreadful undead armies, walls of shadow magika, wield giant bone swords and turn yourself into an abomination of darkness. Control the battlefield  and your victims with the bones of the departed.

State.Author: Mihail

But remember, the Ideal Masters are tricky and greedy, so be carefull, or you will end having your own life drained from inside your body into the dark dunes of Soul Cairn.

State.Author: Mihail

There were once many Crescents, which were used by Dagon's forces to take the Battlespire during the Imperial Simulacrum. When the Empire later reclaimed the ruined academy, the Crescents were gathered up and destroyed - all but one.
State.Name: Daedric Crescent- Mihail Weapons and Shields (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Many daedra prefer to use light daedric armor instead of the traditional heavy variants, likewise many of them also prefer to use lighter and faster weapons, instead of the traditional elaborate heavy armament. This weapon set may not be as robust or powerful as other Oblivion sets, but its slimmer and lighter design allows for faster strikes.
State.Name: Daedric Light Weapons- Mihail Weapons and Shields (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail

When a victim attempts to do so, Mimics will proceed to reveal their dread true form and attack chomping her with their enormous mouth filled with pointed teeth and tearing skin with their long arms with sharp claws.
State.Name: Mimics- Mihail Monsters and Animas (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail

The variant that inhabits Skyrim is among those closest to the original glory and power of its race, unlike other more ferocious variants that live across Tamriel.
